  "prompt": "What is an expression analogous to rest in peace in Hinduism?",
  "response": "In Hinduism, an expression that is often used to convey a similar sentiment to \"rest in peace\" is \"Om Shanti.\" This phrase conveys wishes for peace for the departed soul. Additionally, when mourning, Hindus may say \"Sadgati\" or \"May you attain liberation,\" which reflects the hope for the soul to achieve moksha, or liberation from the cycle of birth and death.",
